BASH COMMANDS:

Command:                        Description:
--------------------------------------------------------
uname -a                        Show system and kernel |
--------------------------------------------------------
head -n1 /etc/issue             Show distribution |
----------------------------------------------------------
mount                           Show mounted filesystems |
----------------------------------------------------------
date                            Show system date |
--------------------------------------------------
uptime                          Show uptime |
----------------------------------------------------
whoami                          Show your username |
---------------------------------------------------------
man <command>                   Show manual for command |
---------------------------------------------------------

<<<----------------------------------------------->>>

DIRECTORY COMMANDS:

Command:                        Description:
------------------------------------------------------------
pwd                             Show the current directory |
------------------------------------------------------------
mkdir <name_of_the_directory>   Make a directory |
--------------------------------------------------
cd <directory>                  Change directory |
--------------------------------------------------------------
cd ..                           Go to the previous directory |
--------------------------------------------------------------
ls                              List files in a directory |
-----------------------------------------------------------

| ls --flags-and-stuff: |

Flag:         Description:
-------------------------------------------------------
-a            Show all files (including hidden files) |
-------------------------------------------------------
-R            Recursive list |
------------------------------
-r            Reverse order |
-----------------------------------
-l            Long listing format |
-------------------------------------               
-t            Sort by last modified |
-------------------------------------
-S            Sort by file size |
---------------------------------
-1            One file per line |
-----------------------------------------
-m            Output separated by comma |
-----------------------------------------
-Q            Quoted output |
-----------------------------

<<<-------------------------------------------------------->>>

FILE PERMISSIONS:

Command:                        Description:
------------------------------------------------------------
chmod 775 <file>                Change mode of file to 775 |
-------------------------------------------------------------------
chmod -R 600 <directory/folder> | Recusiverly chmod folder to 600 |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
chown user:group <file>         Change file owner to user and group to group |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

| FILE PERMISSION NUMBERS: |

Number:         Description:
--------------------------
4               read (r) |
---------------------------
2               write (w) |
-----------------------------
1               execute (x) |
-----------------------------

| FILE OPERATIONS: |

Command:                       Description:
--------------------------------------------
touch <file_name>              Create file |
----------------------------------------------------
cat <file>                     Read a file content |
------------------------------------------------------------------
cat <file_1> <file_2>          Concatenate files and also output |
------------------------------------------------------------------
file <file_1>                  Get type of file |
-------------------------------------------------
mv <file_1> <file_2>           Rename a file |
----------------------------------------------------------
mv <file_1> <new_path>         Move a file to a new path |
---------------------------------------------------------------
scp <file> <new_path>          Safe copy a file to a new path |
---------------------------------------------------------------
cp <file> <new_path>           Copy a file to a new path |
----------------------------------------------------------
rm <file>                      Remove a file |
--------------------------------------------------------------
head <file>                    Show first 10 lines of a file |
--------------------------------------------------------------
tail <file>                    Show last 10 lines of a file |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
tail -F <file>                 Output last lines of a file as it changes |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

<<<------------------------------------------------------->>>

WATCH A COMMAND:

Command:                       Description:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
watch -n 5 '<command>'         Issue the command every 5 seconds and display output |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                                    |
e.g.: watch -n 5 'ntpq -p'                                                        |
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<<<------------------------------------------------------->>>

PROCESS MANAGEMENT:

Command:                      Description:
----------------------------------------------------------
ps                            Show snapshot of processes |
----------------------------------------------------------
top                           Show real time processes |
--------------------------------------------------------
kill <pid>                    Kill process with id pid |
----------------------------------------------------------
pkill <name>                  Kill process with a <name> |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
killall <name>                Kill all processes with names beginning <name> |
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

<<<------------------------------------------------------->>>

BASH SHORTCUTS:

Command:                      Description:
----------------------------------------------
CTRL-r                        Search history |
-------------------------------------------------
CTRL-e                        Go to end of line |
--------------------------------------------------
CTRL-k                        Cut to end of line |
------------------------------------------------------
CTRL-u                        Cut from start of line |
------------------------------------------------------
CTRL-z                        Sleep program |
---------------------------------------------------
CTRL-a                        Go to start of line |
----------------------------------------------------
CTRL-c                        Stop current command |
----------------------------------------------------
!!                            Repeat last command |
------------------------------------------------------------------
!abc                          Run last command starting with abc |
--------------------------------------------------------------------
!abc:p                        Print last command starting with abc |
--------------------------------------------------------------------
!$                            Last argument of previous command |
-----------------------------------------------------------------
ALT-.                         Last argument of previous command |
-----------------------------------------------------------------
!*                            All arguments of previous command |
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
^abc^123                      Run previous command, replacing abc with 123 |
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

<<<-------------------------------------------------------------->>>

BASH VARIABLES:

Command:                      Description:
----------------------------------------------------------
env                           Show environment variables |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
echo $<env_variable>          Output value of <env_variable> variable |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
export <env_variable>=value   Set env_variable to a value |
-----------------------------------------------------------
$PATH                         Executable search path |
------------------------------------------------------
$HOME                         Home directory |
----------------------------------------------
$SHELL                        Current shell |
---------------------------------------------

<<<------------------------------------------------------------->>>

SEARCH FILES:

Command:                      Description:
--------------------------------------------------------------
grep <pattern> <files>        Search for any pattern in fles |
--------------------------------------------------------------
grep -i                       Case insensitive search |
-------------------------------------------------------
grep -r                       Recursive search |
------------------------------------------------
grep -v                       Inverted search |
--------------------------------------------------------------
grep -o                       Show matched part of file only |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
find /directory/ -name <name*> | Find files starting with name in directory |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
find /directory/ -user <name>  | Find files owned by name in directory |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
find /directory/ -mmin <num>  | Find files modified less than num minutes ago in directory |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
whereis <command>             Find a binary / source / manual for a command |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
locate <file>                 Find a file (quick search of system index) |
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

<<<----------------------------------------------------------->>>










